    <title>Hello World: Welcome to My AI Lab</title>
    <link href="/arwin.github.io/2026/02/22/hello-ai/"/>
    <url>/arwin.github.io/2026/02/22/hello-ai/</url>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="Hello-World-Hello-AI"><a href="#Hello-World-Hello-AI" class="headerlink" title="Hello, World. Hello, AI."></a>Hello, World. Hello, AI.</h1><p>Welcome to <strong>Arwin’s AI Lab</strong>.</p><p>I am <strong>Arwin (Haowen Yu)</strong>, a PhD student in Human-Computer Interaction (HCI) and Neuroscience at the University of Glasgow.</p><p>This blog is not just a collection of notes; it is my digital garden where I explore the boundaries of:</p><ul><li><strong>4D Head Avatars</strong> &amp; Neural Rendering</li><li><strong>Affective Computing</strong> (Emotion AI)</li><li><strong>Geometric Deep Learning</strong> (GNNs)</li></ul><p>Here, you will find:</p><ol><li><strong>Deep Dives:</strong> Technical tutorials on core DL algorithms.</li><li><strong>Weekly Pulse:</strong> My curated list of the most important AI news.</li><li><strong>Research:</strong> Updates on my papers and books (including <em>Geometric Deep Learning: Theory and Practice</em>).</li></ol><p>Stay tuned. The future is being decoded.</p><hr><p><em>Powered by Hexo &amp; Fluid.</em></p>]]></content>
    
    
